<subSubSection lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="21" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1520,1886]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis box="[247,357,1747,1772]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lindberg" box="[365,558,1747,1773]" pageId="19" pageNumber="27" refString="Lindberg, H. (1941) Die Hemipteren der Azorischen Inseln. Nebst anhang: Zur Kenntis der Hemipterenfauna von Madeira. Commentationes Biologicae, 8 (8), 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1941">
Lindberg (
<number box="[489,550,1747,1773]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1941.0">1941</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
identified two specimens from Portonovo as 
<taxonomicName authority="Horv. 1908" authorityName="Horv." authorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Hyalesthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angustulus">
<emphasis box="[1098,1362,1747,1772]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Hyalesthes angustulus</emphasis>
Horv. 
<number box="[247,306,1785,1811]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1908.0">1908</number>
</taxonomicName>
but later (
<number box="[449,510,1785,1811]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1961.0">1961</number>
) he identified them as 
<taxonomicName box="[816,1088,1785,1810]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Hyalesthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipennis">
<emphasis box="[816,1088,1785,1810]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Hyalesthes flavipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Remane" box="[1110,1436,1785,1811]" pageId="19" pageNumber="26" refString="Hoch, H. &amp; Remane, R. (1985) Evolution und speziation der zikaden - gattung Hyalesthes Signoret, 1865 (Homoptera, Auchenorrhycha, Fulgoroidea, Cixiidae). Marburger Entomologische Publikationen, 2 (2), 1 - 427." type="journal article" year="1985">
Remane and Hoch (
<number box="[1366,1427,1785,1811]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" value="1985.0">1985</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName box="[369,537,1823,1848]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Hyalesthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="portonoves">
<emphasis box="[369,537,1823,1848]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">H. portonoves</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the same locality; therefore, it is very likely that Lindbergâ€™s material corresponds to this species.
</paragraph>
